## RLS matrix (24 tables)

| Table | RLS | Policy coverage notes |
|-------|-----|------------------------|
| `households` | ✅ | SELECT/UPDATE via `is_household_member(id)`; INSERT authenticated |
| `household_members` | ✅ | SELECT via `is_household_member`; INSERT own `user_id`; UPDATE own row |
| `household_items` | ✅ | SELECT/INSERT/UPDATE for members — **no DELETE** |
| `household_item_aliases` | ✅ | Full CRUD for members |
| `household_guests` | ✅ | Full CRUD for members |
| `household_guest_groups` | ✅ | Full CRUD for members |
| `household_guest_group_members` | ✅ | ALL via group → household membership |
| `receipts` | ✅ | SELECT/INSERT for members — **no UPDATE/DELETE** |
| `receipt_line_items` | ✅ | SELECT/INSERT via receipt → household — **no UPDATE/DELETE** |
| `meal_logs` | ✅ | SELECT/INSERT for household; DELETE own `made_by_member_id` — **no UPDATE** |
| `recurring_payment_reports` | ✅ | Member ALL own rows; payer SELECT on their recurring expenses |
| `household_events` | ✅ | SELECT/INSERT/DELETE for members; INSERT requires `created_by` = caller's member id — **no UPDATE** |
| `shopping_lists` | ⚠️ | **No RLS** — exposed via anon key |
| `shopping_list_items` | ⚠️ | **No RLS** |
| `recipes` | ⚠️ | **No RLS** |
| `recipe_ingredients` | ⚠️ | **No RLS** |
| `recipe_steps` | ⚠️ | **No RLS** |
| `recipe_tags` | ⚠️ | **No RLS** |
| `expense_categories` | ⚠️ | **No RLS** |
| `category_splits` | ⚠️ | **No RLS** |
| `expenses` | ⚠️ | **No RLS** |
| `expense_splits` | ⚠️ | **No RLS** |
| `recurring_expenses` | ⚠️ | **No RLS** |
| `recurring_expense_splits` | ⚠️ | **No RLS** |

**Counts:** 12 with RLS ✅ · 12 without ⚠️

Do **not** `ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` without policies — that blocks all access. See [Supabase RLS](https://supabase.com/docs/guides/database/postgres/row-level-security).

